## Monitoring and Logging

### CloudWatch Monitoring

#### Accessing Logs

##### Via AWS Console
1. Navigate to CloudWatch service
2. Select "Log groups" from left menu
3. Find log groups:
   - `/aws/apigateway/hello-world-api`
   - `/aws/lambda/hello-world-function`

##### Via AWS CLI
```bash
# View API Gateway logs
aws logs tail /aws/apigateway/hello-world-api --follow

# View Lambda logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/hello-world-function --follow

# Get specific log events
aws logs get-log-events \
  --log-group-name /aws/lambda/hello-world-function \
  --log-stream-name "2026/04/13/[$LATEST]abcd1234" \
  --start-time 1649800000000
```

### Key Metrics to Monitor

#### API Gateway Metrics
- **Request Count**: Number of API requests
- **Latency**: Response time distribution
- **Error Rate**: 4xx and 5xx error percentages
- **Data Transfer**: Amount of data transferred

#### Lambda Metrics
- **Invocation Count**: Number of function invocations
- **Duration**: Function execution time
- **Error Rate**: Function error percentage
- **Concurrent Executions**: Number of concurrent function instances

### Setting Up Alarms

#### High Error Rate Alarm
```bash
aws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \
  --alarm-name "API-High-Error-Rate" \
  --alarm-description "API Gateway 5xx error rate > 5%" \
  --metric-name 5XXError \
  --namespace AWS/ApiGateway \
  --statistic Sum \
  --period 300 \
  --threshold 5 \
  --comparison-operator GreaterThanThreshold \
  --dimensions Name=ApiName,Value=hello-world-api
```

### Log Analysis

#### Common Log Patterns
```
# API Gateway Access Log Format
{ "requestId": "abcd-1234", "ip": "192.168.1.1", "requestTime": "13/Apr/2026:10:30:00 +0000", "httpMethod": "GET", "resourcePath": "/", "status": "200", "protocol": "HTTP/1.1", "responseLength": "123" }

# Lambda Function Log Format
START RequestId: abcd-1234 Version: $LATEST
2026-04-13T10:30:00.000Z	abcd-1234	INFO	Processing request
END RequestId: abcd-1234
REPORT RequestId: abcd-1234	Duration: 15.00 ms	Billed Duration: 16 ms	Memory Size: 128 MB	Max Memory Used: 64 MB
```

