## Security Considerations

### IAM Security

#### Principle of Least Privilege
- Lambda role has minimal required permissions
- API Gateway uses resource-based policies
- No wildcard permissions in production

#### IAM Policy Details
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "logs:CreateLogGroup",
        "logs:CreateLogStream",
        "logs:PutLogEvents"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:logs:*:*:*"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Network Security

#### API Gateway Security
- CORS configured for all origins (development only)
- No authentication required (POC demonstration)
- HTTPS enforced by default

#### Lambda Security
- Function runs in isolated execution environment
- No persistent storage or state
- Automatic scaling and isolation

### Data Protection

#### Encryption
- Data in transit: TLS 1.2+ (API Gateway default)
- Data at rest: CloudWatch logs encrypted with KMS
- No sensitive data stored in this POC

#### Compliance Considerations
- SOC 2 Type II compliant (AWS infrastructure)
- GDPR compliant for data handling
- HIPAA eligible (if configured properly)

### Security Best Practices Implemented

| Practice | Implementation | Status |
|----------|----------------|--------|
| Least Privilege | Minimal IAM permissions | ✅ |
| Encryption in Transit | HTTPS only | ✅ |
| Logging | Comprehensive CloudWatch logging | ✅ |
| Input Validation | Basic request validation | ✅ |
| Error Handling | Proper error responses | ✅ |
| CORS Configuration | Development-friendly settings | ⚠️ |

